	(text "Smart stethoscope - reverse-engineered system interconnect (Premium build)"
		(exclude_from_sim no)(at 300.00 20.00 0)
		(effects (font (size 3.0 3.0) (bold yes)))(uuid "0b171bda-19a5-4157-85e3-942c91ee2d3b"))
	(text "Reconstructed from the owner-held design spec; NOT verified against the metal. Every net colour = confidence. No net is green: nothing is continuity-verified yet."
		(exclude_from_sim no)(at 300.00 30.00 0)
		(effects (font (size 1.6 1.6)))(uuid "220936b4-5dcb-4826-b478-7b94c21c3bdb"))
	(text_box "CONFIDENCE (wire colour)\n\nGREEN  = verified by continuity  (none yet - pre-teardown)\nBLUE   = vendor design spec (block diagram / bus map / power table)\nORANGE = datasheet-fixed / typical app circuit\nRED    = unknown / bench-TBD\n\nThis sheet is EVIDENCE, not a design. A net that looks certain but\nis only inferred is worse than an honest hole. Re-open in eeschema\nand recolour a net GREEN only after buzzing it out on the bench."
		(exclude_from_sim no)(at 25.00 415.00 0)(size 258.00 120.00)
		(margins 1.27 1.27 1.27 1.27)(stroke (width 0.2)(type default))
		(fill (type color)(color 232 232 232 1))(effects (font (size 1.0 1.0)) (justify left top))(uuid "11b8b260-bca4-4fa4-ab8a-14abd297fe50"))
	(text_box "NET CONFIDENCE LEDGER  (authoritative list - every net + basis)\n\n[V] VERIFIED (continuity)  -  0 net(s)\n      (none)\n\n[S] SPEC (vendor design spec)  -  39 net(s)\n      I2C0_SCL       spec bus map: I2C0 SCL, 1.8V (IMU 0x1E, codec 0x0A, gauge 0x16, FPGA TBD)\n      I2C0_SDA       spec bus map: I2C0 SDA, 1.8V\n      I2C2_SCL       spec bus map: I2C2 SCL, 1.8V (touch 0x64, GPIO 0x40)\n      I2C2_SDA       spec bus map: I2C2 SDA, 1.8V\n      SPI1_SCK       spec bus map: SPI1 clock, 1.8V\n      SPI1_MOSI      spec bus map: SPI1 MOSI, 1.8V\n      SPI1_MISO      spec bus map: SPI1 MISO, 1.8V\n      SPI1_CS0_DISP  spec: SPI1 PCS0 = display (through FPGA)\n      SPI1_CS1_FLASH spec: SPI1 PCS1 = flash\n      SPI1_CS2_FPGA  spec: SPI1 PCS2 = FPGA registers\n      I2S0_TXD       spec: I2S0 CPU->FPGA/codec data (CPU is I2S master)\n      I2S0_RXD       spec: I2S0 codec->CPU data\n      I2S0_MCLK      spec: I2S0 MCLK, CPU->codec/FPGA\n      I2S0_BCLK      spec: I2S0 bit clock\n      I2S0_LRCLK     spec: I2S0 L/R clock (8 kHz); FPGA mic clock locks to this x64\n      UART0_TX_BT    spec: UART0 CPU->BC127\n      UART0_RX_BT    spec: UART0 BC127->CPU\n      XTAL_16M       spec clock topology: 16 MHz crystal -> CPU EXTAL0/XTAL0\n      XTAL_32K       spec: 32.768 kHz osc -> CPU RTC + audio subsection\n      CLK60M_FPGA    spec: CPU MCGOUTCLK 120M / OUTDIV4 = 60 MHz -> FPGA PLL (sysclk 64 MHz)\n      MIC_PDM_CLK    spec: FPGA-generated mic master clock (<=2.4 MHz), PLL-locked to I2S L/R x64\n      DISP_SCK       spec: display SPI clock via FPGA\n      DISP_MOSI      spec: display SPI data via FPGA\n      CHARGE_n       spec: CHARGE input CPU PTA24 (ball K11) low = charging; charge LED direct from charger\n      IRQ_LLWU_P8    spec: touch/GPIO INT -> CPU LLWU_P8 (PTC4, spec 'pin B8') low-power wakeup\n      BLE_RESET_n    spec register map reg1 bit4 BLE_RESET_N: FPGA controls BC127 reset\n      BLE_VREG_EN    spec register map reg1 bit5 BLE_VREG_EN: FPGA controls BC127 regulator\n      TOUCH_ELEC     spec: 3 touch buttons (TZ0-2) + right-edge slider (wheel2) electrodes\n      UI_LED         spec: 6-7 UI LEDs via touch ctlr (Premium) or GPIO expander (Economy)\n      BTN            spec: 4 push buttons SW1-4 via GPIO expander (Economy variant)\n      HP_L           spec: codec headphone-L -> 3.5mm jack\n      HP_R           spec: codec headphone-R -> 3.5mm jack\n      COIL           spec: Rx coil -> BQ51050B AC1/AC2 (Qi, Premium)\n      +VBAT          spec: Li-Po ~4.2 V -> PMIC input; charger output\n      +1V8           spec power table: 1.8 V rail (CPU core/dig, SDRAM, flash, mics, codec-dig, touch, 1.8V IO)\n      +3V3           spec power table: 3.3 V rail (codec analog, IMU, FPGA core/VCCA, BC127, display)\n      +3V3A          spec power sequence: 3.3 Va rail (1.8 -> 3.3 -> 3.3Va -> 2.5)\n      +2V5           spec power sequence: 2.5 V rail\n      GND            common ground / shield can / battery negative\n\n[D] DATASHEET-fixed / typical  -  6 net(s)\n      SWD_CLK        MK26 datasheet: PTA0 JTAG_TCLK/SWD_CLK, 169-MAPBGA ball N8 (fixed-function)\n      SWD_DIO        MK26 datasheet: PTA3 JTAG_TMS/SWD_DIO, ball M8 (fixed-function)\n      SWO_TDO        MK26 datasheet: PTA2 JTAG_TDO/TRACE_SWO, ball M9 (fixed-function)\n      JTAG_TDI       MK26 datasheet: PTA1 JTAG_TDI, ball N9 (fixed-function)\n      NMI_b          MK26 datasheet: PTA4 NMI_b/LLWU_P3, ball L9\n      RESET_b        MK26 datasheet: RESET_b, ball L13; pull-up to VDD expected\n\n[?] UNKNOWN / bench-TBD  -  10 net(s)\n      MIC_MCLK       spec 'MIC_MASTER_CLK 16 MHz, CPU pin 46' -- 169-MAPBGA ball for 'pin 46' unresolved; relation to CLK60M unclear\n      PDM_D0         spec: 6 PDM streams mics->FPGA; exact line count/pairing (6 data vs 3 L/R-shared) bench-TBD\n      PDM_D1         spec: PDM mic data group; grouping bench-TBD\n      PDM_D2         spec: PDM mic data group (incl. Mic5 ambient); grouping bench-TBD\n      DISP_CTRL      EPD D/C, RST, BUSY typical control lines; FPGA/CPU pin assignment bench-TBD\n      SDRAM_A        spec: 128Mbit x16 LPSDR on CPU SDRAM/FlexBus; exact address mapping bench-TBD\n      SDRAM_DQ       spec: SDRAM x16 data; exact FlexBus data mapping bench-TBD\n      SDRAM_CTRL     spec: SDRAM CLK/CKE/CS/RAS/CAS/WE/DQM; exact control mapping bench-TBD\n      IMU_INT        IMU INT1/INT2 present in datasheet; CPU pin bench-TBD\n      5V_DC_IN       Economy wired-charge path via mic jack; NOT populated on Premium bench unit\n"
		(exclude_from_sim no)(at 295.00 415.00 0)(size 470.00 152.00)
		(margins 1.27 1.27 1.27 1.27)(stroke (width 0.2)(type default))
		(fill (type color)(color 248 248 248 1))(effects (font (size 0.8 0.8)) (justify left top))(uuid "4d76fc1c-0450-4201-b08b-0372cde9e115"))
